# Environment Variables for One ID

## Vercel Environment Variables (Backend)
# Add these in Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables

# Supabase Configuration (Required)
SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJxxx...

# Cron Job Secret (Required for cleanup)
CRON_SECRET=your-random-secret-here

# Optional: Stripe for real virtual cards
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx

# Optional: Twilio for real SMS
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxx
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=xxx
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+1xxx


## Client Environment Variables
# Add these in Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables
# OR create client/.env.local for local development

# Supabase Configuration (Required)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJxxx...


## Local Development
# Create a .env file in the root directory with:

SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJxxx...
CRON_SECRET=test-secret


## How to Get Supabase Keys

1. Go to https://supabase.com
2. Create a new project
3. Go to Settings → API
4. Copy:
   - Project URL → SUPABASE_URL
   - service_role key → SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
   - anon public key → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
